body_md:
やっほー、しぃちゃんだよ！今日は Durable Objects のテストがちょっと楽になるお知らせを見つけたから紹介するね。

## なにが発表されたの？

Cloudflare の Changelog で、`@cloudflare/vitest-pool-workers` に `evictDurableObject` と `evictAllDurableObjects` っていう 2 つのテストヘルパーが追加されたよ。どっちも `cloudflare:test` からインポートして、Vitest のテストの中で使えるの。

## 今までどうだったの？

Durable Object って、アイドル状態が続くとメモリから追い出される（evict される）ことがあるの。これは本番の [Durable Object のライフサイクル](https://developers.cloudflare.com/durable-objects/concepts/durable-object-lifecycle/)では普通に起きること。でも「追い出されたあとにちゃんと状態が復元されるかな？」ってテストしたくても、その追い出しを自分のタイミングで再現する手段がなかったんだよね。

## これで何が変わるの？

新しいヘルパーを呼べば、テストの中で好きなタイミングで eviction を起こせるようになったの。ストレージから状態がちゃんと読み直されるか、WebSocket まわりの挙動はどうか、みたいなところを実際に確かめられるようになるよ。

## 深く潜ってみよう

使い方はこんな感じだよ。

```ts
import { evictDurableObject, evictAllDurableObjects } from "cloudflare:test";
import { env } from "cloudflare:workers";

const id = env.COUNTER.idFromName("my-counter");
const stub = env.COUNTER.get(id);

// 特定の stub が指す Durable Object を追い出す
await evictDurableObject(stub);

// WebSocket をハイバネートせずに閉じる
await evictDurableObject(stub, { webSockets: "close" });

// evict 可能な namespace で動いてる Durable Object を全部追い出す
await evictAllDurableObjects();
```

`evictDurableObject` は stub を 1 つ渡すと、その instance だけを追い出せるの。`{ webSockets: "close" }` を付けると、ハイバネーションじゃなくて WebSocket を閉じる挙動を試せるよ。`evictAllDurableObjects` は evict 可能な namespace で動いてるやつを一気に全部。使えるのは `@cloudflare/vitest-pool-workers@0.16.20` 以降だよ。もっと詳しくは [Test APIs リファレンス](https://developers.cloudflare.com/workers/testing/vitest-integration/test-apis/#durable-objects)と [Testing Durable Objects ガイド](https://developers.cloudflare.com/durable-objects/examples/testing-with-durable-objects/#testing-eviction)を見てね。

## まとめ

- `evictDurableObject` と `evictAllDurableObjects` が `cloudflare:test` に追加されたよ
- テストの中で eviction を再現できて、追い出し後の状態復元や WebSocket の挙動を確かめられるの
- `{ webSockets: "close" }` を付けると WebSocket を閉じる挙動も試せる
- 使えるのは `@cloudflare/vitest-pool-workers@0.16.20` 以降

Durable Objects でステートフルなアプリを書いてて、テストもきっちり固めたい人にぴったりのアップデートだよ！

body_md_en:
Hey there, it's me, Shiichan! Today I found a little update that makes testing Durable Objects a bit nicer, so let me share it with you.

## What was announced?

On the Cloudflare Changelog, two new test helpers, `evictDurableObject` and `evictAllDurableObjects`, were added to `@cloudflare/vitest-pool-workers`. Both are imported from `cloudflare:test` and used inside your Vitest tests.

## The story so far

A Durable Object can be evicted from memory when it stays idle for a while. That's a normal part of the production [Durable Object lifecycle](https://developers.cloudflare.com/durable-objects/concepts/durable-object-lifecycle/). But when you wanted to test whether your state gets restored correctly after an eviction, there was no way to reproduce that eviction on your own schedule.

## What changes

With the new helpers, you can now trigger eviction at any point inside a test. That lets you actually check whether state is re-read from storage, and how your WebSocket behavior holds up.

## Dive Deep

Here is how you use them.

```ts
import { evictDurableObject, evictAllDurableObjects } from "cloudflare:test";
import { env } from "cloudflare:workers";

const id = env.COUNTER.idFromName("my-counter");
const stub = env.COUNTER.get(id);

// Evict the Durable Object instance pointed to by a specific stub
await evictDurableObject(stub);

// Close WebSockets instead of hibernating them
await evictDurableObject(stub, { webSockets: "close" });

// Evict all currently-running Durable Objects in evictable namespaces
await evictAllDurableObjects();
```

Pass a single stub to `evictDurableObject` and it evicts just that instance. Add `{ webSockets: "close" }` to test the behavior where WebSockets are closed instead of hibernated. `evictAllDurableObjects` clears out every running instance in evictable namespaces at once. These are available in `@cloudflare/vitest-pool-workers@0.16.20` and later. For more, check the [Test APIs reference](https://developers.cloudflare.com/workers/testing/vitest-integration/test-apis/#durable-objects) and the [Testing Durable Objects guide](https://developers.cloudflare.com/durable-objects/examples/testing-with-durable-objects/#testing-eviction).

## Wrap-up

- `evictDurableObject` and `evictAllDurableObjects` were added to `cloudflare:test`
- You can reproduce eviction in a test and verify state restoration and WebSocket behavior afterward
- Add `{ webSockets: "close" }` to test closing WebSockets instead of hibernating
- Available in `@cloudflare/vitest-pool-workers@0.16.20` and later

This one is perfect for anyone building stateful apps with Durable Objects who also wants to lock down their tests!
